issue.title: kill poedat.erosson.org
issue.body: leave it online for a few months, just in case anyone's using it. give people some time to see the project is retired. then kill it

comment.body:
It's alright, I understand how these sorts of projects go, it's just the normal cycle of things.  
In terms of the poe-dat-viewer, it definitely has all the data I need, the only issue is how it's accessed, I'm automating a bunch of things around the data and having to manually download and ingress each json file is a massive pain.
The API you provided has made that process a lot easier

issue.title: kill poedat.erosson.org
issue.body: leave it online for a few months, just in case anyone's using it. give people some time to see the project is retired. then kill it

comment.body:
Thanks for the work you've done on this project.  
I have some tools that rely on the outputs here and poe-dat-viewer isn't a suitable replacement.  
I'll start looking around for something that I might be able to use as instead
